# CursorRules for 长话短说Bot

## Development Mode Guidelines

### Interface-First Principle
- Complete interface definition required before module development
- Interface definition must include:
  - Function signatures/API endpoints
  - Input parameter types and constraints
  - Return value types and formats
  - Error handling methods
  - Usage examples

### Natural Language Driven Development
- Use natural language for development requirements
- Each task must include:
  - User scenario description
  - Input/output examples
  - Error handling expectations
  - Boundary conditions

### Test-Driven Development
- Use natural language for test cases
- Each test must include:
  - Test purpose
  - Test data
  - Expected results
  - Boundary conditions

## Code Quality Control

### Code Standards
- Follow project code style guidelines
- Each file must include:
  - File header comments (purpose, author, date)
  - Key function comments
  - Complex logic explanations

### Error Handling
- Unified error handling mechanism
- Each error must include:
  - Error type
  - Error description
  - Error code
  - Handling suggestions

### Logging Standards
- Unified log format
- Standardized log levels
- Required logging for key operations

## Version Control Guidelines

### Feature Release Management
- Each feature release must provide:
  - Feature documentation
  - Interface change documentation
  - Test reports
  - Deployment instructions

### Version Number Management
- Follow semantic versioning
- Version format: major.minor.patch
- Version number must be updated for each release

## Documentation Standards

### API Documentation
- Use Swagger/OpenAPI standards
- Documentation must include:
  - API descriptions
  - Request/response examples
  - Error code explanations
  - Usage instructions

### Development Documentation
- Each module must provide:
  - Module description
  - Architecture design
  - Key processes
  - Important notes

